{"data": [{"id": "4742280", "title": "Hims & Hers Vs. Amazon: Why David Defeats Goliath", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"David and Goliath on the house wall ,Regensburg,unesco heritage\" data-id=\"153701304\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1021px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">kaetana_istock</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Thesis Summary</h2> <p><strong>Hims &amp; Hers</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HIMS\" title=\"Hims &amp; Hers Health, Inc.\">HIMS</a></span>) has been on a monster rally in the last year, as it has become a dominant player in the telehealth market.</p> <p>The only real threat to this company, right now, seems to be competition.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/153701304/image_153701304.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742280-hims-and-hers-vs-amazon-why-david-defeats-goliath", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 14:16:30"}, {"id": "4742291", "title": "Is U.S. Economic Growth Accelerating In Q4?", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Business and Leadership Success\" data-id=\"1474796041\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1072px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">We Are</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>The odds still look skewed toward a softer pace of expansion for fourth-quarter GDP, but an upgraded nowcast from the Atlanta Fed hints at the possibility for something stronger.</p> <p>The regional Fed bank\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.atlantafed.org/cqer/research/gdpnow\" rel=\"noopener\">GDPNow model</a> lifted its</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1474796041/image_1474796041.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742291-is-us-economic-growth-accelerating-in-q4", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 14:15:00"}, {"id": "4742286", "title": "A Passive Income Solution Without The Volatility", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Business Professionals in a Meeting Brainstorming Ideas and Discussing Financial Data and Statistics\" data-id=\"1887449055\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1025px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">LaylaBird</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><em>By Kevin Flanagan</em></p> <p>With the U.S. interest rate landscape returning to a more historically normal setting over the last year or so, investors are now presented with a backdrop that hasn't been witnessed in literally more than a decade. As a result, I</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1887449055/image_1887449055.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742286-passive-income-solution-without-volatility", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:50:00"}, {"id": "4742285", "title": "What's Next For Global Monetary Policy?", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Business consept image Financial graphs\" data-id=\"1197543861\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Ca-ssis</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <p><em>By Erik Norland</em></p> <h2>At a Glance</h2> <ul> <li>Lingering core inflation is complicating central banks' efforts to balance growth and inflation risks</li> <li>Futures curves suggest further rate cuts could be ahead for multiple countries</li> </ul> <p><em>2024 was a global turning point for monetary policy. After two years of massive policy tightening, central banks began to ease policy pretty much across the board. What might be in store for 2025?</em></p> <p><figure class=\"sa-widget sa-embed\" data-id=\"28167\" data-category=\"video\" data-provider=\"Brightcove\" data-thumbnail=\"https://cf-images.us-east-1.prod.boltdns.net/v1/static/49919183001/0f9c1abc-7fe3-4523-a859-7a62b771ce06/c8c23482-1281-47ac-988a-621414d63b04/1280x720/match/image.jpg\"><iframe src=\"https://seekingalpha.com/embed/28167\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"sa-embed-iframe embed-responsive-item\" data-original-width=\"640\" data-original-height=\"360\" data-id=\"28167\" data-category=\"video\" data-provider=\"Brightcove\"></iframe></figure></p> <p>Going into next year, futures curves for SOFR, Euro ESTR and analogous products on other markets, suggest that traders still see some room for further interest rate reduction in the U.S., the eurozone, the U.K., Australia and Canada. Recently, however, traders have curtailed these expectations for rate cuts.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/5/55028208-17333944961917336_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"942\" data-height=\"654\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/5/55028208-17333944961917336.png\" alt=\"interest rate expectations as of nov. 21, 2024\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture></figure></p> <p>While inflation is way down from its peak levels in 2022 and 2023, it has stopped falling in many countries and remains about 1-2% above pre-pandemic levels.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/5/55028208-173339452029718_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"947\" data-height=\"658\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/5/55028208-173339452029718.png\" alt=\"Core Inflation\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture></figure></p> <p>In the U.S. for example, core inflation has stabilized at around 3.3% for the past six months, while its pre-pandemic level was typically closer to the Fed's target of 2%.</p> <p>This creates a dilemma for the Fed and other central banks. On the one hand, they might like to cut rates further, especially if economic growth slows in response to their policy tightening in 2022 and 2023, which was the largest in over forty years. On the other hand, persistent core inflation might give them pause, especially if further rate cuts risk igniting second rounds of inflation later this decade.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.cmegroup.com/openmarkets/economics/2024/Whats-Next-for-Global-Monetary-Policy.html?source=rss\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener noopener\">Original Post</a></p> <div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder\"></div><p><strong>Editor's Note:</strong> The summary bullets for this article were chosen by Seeking Alpha editors.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1197543861/image_1197543861.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742285-whats-next-for-global-monetary-policy", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:40:00"}, {"id": "4742275", "title": "Teleperformance: Very Interesting Trends, A Continued 'Buy' For Me", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt='Exterior view of the teleperformance building, showcasing the company\"s modern architecture' data-id=\"2168935235\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">joao malaquias</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Dear readers and subscribers,</p> <p>If you follow my work, you know that I have a significant investment in <strong>Teleperformance</strong> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TLPFY\" title=\"Teleperformance SE\" target=\"_blank\">OTCPK:TLPFY</a>). For me, significant is an investment that is above 2% of my total portfolio - and this is the case</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2168935235/image_2168935235.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742275-teleperformance-very-interesting-trends-a-continued-buy-for-me", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:35:08"}, {"id": "4742282", "title": "Comparing The S&P Quality FCF Aristocrats Indices With The S&P Dividend Aristocrats", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Standard &amp; Poors in NY\" data-id=\"469565348\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"5302px\" height=\"3535px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">mixmotive</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><em>By Elizabeth Bebb</em></p> <p>While the S&amp;P Dividend Aristocrats\u00ae Indices have been in existence for almost two decades, only now has the \"Aristocrats\" moniker been extended to a new series: the S&amp;P Quality FCF Aristocrats\u00ae (Free Cash Flow Aristocrats) Indices. Like the S&amp;P Dividend Aristocrats, this new series emphasizes</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/469565348/image_469565348.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742282-comparing-sp-quality-fcf-aristocrats-indices-with-sp-dividend-aristocrats", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:30:00"}, {"id": "4742270", "title": "Peloton Interactive: Subscriber Losses And Dilution Create Headwinds", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Man using his indoor bike turbo trainer at home in the evening\" data-id=\"1369193071\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Justin Paget</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Introduction</h2> <p>I <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4636258-peloton-pton-stock-uphill-battle-bearish-outlook\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4636258-peloton-pton-stock-uphill-battle-bearish-outlook\" target=\"_blank\">previously</a> gave Peloton Interactive (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PTON\" title=\"Peloton Interactive, Inc.\">PTON</a></span>), the connected fitness equipment and subscription company, a strong sell rating last October when it traded at $4.67 a share, due to its ongoing operational challenges, high debt levels, and declining revenue. Following a brief increase, the shares</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1369193071/image_1369193071.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742270-peloton-interactive-subscriber-losses-and-dilution-create-headwinds-pton-stock", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:25:00"}, {"id": "4742258", "title": "Asset Class Scoreboard: November 2024", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Modern working desk with digital tablet\" data-id=\"171331544\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1022px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">courtneyk</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>The November asset class scoreboard paints a nuanced picture of the investment landscape in the wake of the recent election. Concerns about potential political instability or market volatility proved unfounded, as the democratic process unfolded with integrity, allaying previous anxieties. In fact, U.S. equities</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/171331544/image_171331544.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742258-asset-class-scoreboard-november-2024", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:15:00"}, {"id": "4742267", "title": "Accolade: A GARP Stock Trading Well Under 1X Revenues", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Health Benefits Claim Form\" data-id=\"165871895\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1022px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">teekid</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>It\u2019s tax loss time. Investors sell their losers late in the year for a tax benefit, further driving down stocks already beaten down. This is the time of the year to buy those stocks to play the January Effect, which bets on a recovery</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165871895/image_165871895.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742267-accolade-accd-stock-garp-stock-trading-well-under-1x-revenues", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:05:04"}, {"id": "4742173", "title": "Buy The Post-Election Healthcare Dip With These Stocks", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt='Close-up Shot of a Doctor\"s Hand Pointing on Brain Scan Images on Digital Tablet' data-id=\"2148728482\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1025px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Tom Werner</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Healthcare Stocks Miss Out on \u2018Trump Bump\u2019</h2> <p>Donald Trump\u2019s presidential victory was a boon for some of America\u2019s largest corporations, with the S&amp;P 500 <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4336181-sp500-nasdaq-dow-jones-outlook-stock-market\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4336181-sp500-nasdaq-dow-jones-outlook-stock-market\" target=\"_blank\">reaching new heights this week</a>, as investors set aside worries of potential tariffs and the Federal<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> Reserve signaled further interest rate cuts.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Meanwhile, the SPDR S&amp;P 500 ETF Trust (NYSEARCA: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPY\" title=\"SPDR\u00ae S&amp;P 500 ETF Trust\">SPY</a>) rallied more than 2.4% from November 5 to November 20 at the prospect that a second Trump administration could bring lower taxes and deregulation.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">However, healthcare companies have missed out on much of the \u2018Trump Bump\u2019 enjoyed by financial services, tech, energy, and other major industries. The S&amp;P Healthcare (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XLV\" title=\"Health Care Select Sector SPDR\u00ae Fund ETF\">XLV</a>) index has lost 1.2% since November 5 as investors <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4292433-vaccines-makers-close-lower-on-reports-rfk-jr-may-head-hhs\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4292433-vaccines-makers-close-lower-on-reports-rfk-jr-may-head-hhs\" target=\"_blank\">digested</a> the nomination of Robert F. Kennedy Jr to lead the US Department of Health and Human Services.</p> <figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_aa6a70e4f22356e7396373f510629eae.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1600\" data-height=\"1080\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_aa6a70e4f22356e7396373f510629eae_thumb1.png\" alt=\"chart\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Seeking Alpha Premium</span></p></figcaption></figure><p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Kennedy's political ascent\u2014a <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4737890-big-pharma-reckoning-looms-with-rfk-jr-eyeing-pfizer\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4737890-big-pharma-reckoning-looms-with-rfk-jr-eyeing-pfizer\" target=\"_blank\">vocal skeptic</a> of vaccines and weight-loss drugs, two of the healthcare industry\u2019s biggest moneymakers\u2014has unleashed fresh volatility in what looked to be a lucrative new chapter for biotech and Big Pharma. Both sectors had hoped to get a boost from waning interest rates and a potentially less aggressive antitrust regime under Trump.</p> <h2 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Bright Spots for Value-Seekers</h2> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">It\u2019s no secret that the Healthcare Sector (XLV) has been one of the worst-performing sectors over the past year, it\u2019s not all doom and gloom for <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/market-news/healthcare\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/market-news/healthcare\" target=\"_blank\">healthcare stocks</a>. Like in any market sell-off, there are attractive discounts to be gleaned for savvy value investors.</p> <figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_d15e1efea95fd1c34dd7f26f31cb3d50.jpeg\" rel=\"lightbox\" title=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_d15e1efea95fd1c34dd7f26f31cb3d50.jpeg\" target=\"_blank\" data-width=\"1380\" data-height=\"612\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_d15e1efea95fd1c34dd7f26f31cb3d50_thumb1.jpeg\" alt=\"chart\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Seeking Alpha Premium</span></p></figcaption></figure><p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The uncertainty surrounding the incoming Trump administration\u2019s approach to healthcare regulation has created buying opportunities, as Morningstar Equity Research <a href=\"https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/healthcare-stocks-got-crushed-after-electionis-it-time-buy\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/healthcare-stocks-got-crushed-after-electionis-it-time-buy\" target=\"_blank\">highlights</a>:</p> <blockquote class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> <p> </p> <p><span class=\"highlighted_text\">The [healthcare] sector is trading at a discount of 6.6% overall, according to Morningstar\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.morningstar.com/markets/fair-value?market=healthcare\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"https://www.morningstar.com/markets/fair-value?market=healthcare\" target=\"_blank\">fair value estimates</a>. Investors can still find opportunities, especially since the overall US market is trading at a premium of about 5%.</span></p> <p>\"With healthcare companies trading well below Morningstar\u2019s estimates of their fair values, a lot of bad news is baked into the price, <a href=\"https://www.morningstar.com/markets/markets-brief-time-look-healthcare-stocks-again\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"https://www.morningstar.com/markets/markets-brief-time-look-healthcare-stocks-again\" target=\"_blank\">increasing the probability of a positive surprise</a>,\u201d wrote Morningstar chief research and investment officer <a href=\"https://www.morningstar.com/people/dan-kemp\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"https://www.morningstar.com/people/dan-kemp\" target=\"_blank\">Dan Kemp</a> last week.</p> </blockquote> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">SA\u2019s Quant system ranks the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/96793114-Top-Healthcare-Stocks\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/96793114-Top-Healthcare-Stocks\" target=\"_blank\">Top Healthcare Stocks</a> by evaluating each company\u2019s financial performance in terms of valuation, growth, momentum, profitability, and more.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Here are two standout healthcare stocks with <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/95b9990b-Top-Stocks-by-Quant\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/95b9990b-Top-Stocks-by-Quant\" target=\"_blank\">\u2018Strong Buy\u2019</a> Quant ratings\u2014the result of our proprietary computer processing technology and what I call \u2018quantamental\u2019 analysis\u2014currently trading at deep discounts from the rest of the sector.</p> <h3 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">1. Exelixis (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EXEL\" title=\"Exelixis, Inc.\">EXEL</a>)</h3> <ul class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> <li><p>Market Capitalization: $10.16B</p></li> <li><p>Quant Rating: Strong Buy</p></li> <li><p>Quant Sector Ranking (as of 12/3/24): 21 out of 1020</p></li> <li><p>Quant Industry Ranking (as of 12/3/24): 7 out of 497</p></li> </ul> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Exelixis is a biotech company based in Alameda, California, focused on developing new medicines for difficult-to-treat cancers. Following a successful third quarter and blockbuster year overall, the company raised its revenue guidance to $2.15B-$2.2B, up from $1.975B-$2.075B.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Shares in the company have rallied more than 65% over the past 12 months on the back of a successful year\u2014its main product is Cabometyx, a drug for renal cell carcinoma and other cancers, which generated $478.1M during the third quarter of 2024, according to its latest <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4730711-exelixis-inc-exel-q3-2024-earnings-call-transcript\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4730711-exelixis-inc-exel-q3-2024-earnings-call-transcript\" target=\"_blank\">earnings</a>. EXEL\u2019s breakthrough next-generation cancer drug Zanzalintinib has also emerged as a powerful future growth engine.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Zanzalintinib is poised to grow into a $5B yearly revenue asset by 2033, writes SA analyst Myriam Alvarez, <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4731408-exelixis-cabometyx-drives-revenue-zanzalintinib-emerges-future-growth-engine\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4731408-exelixis-cabometyx-drives-revenue-zanzalintinib-emerges-future-growth-engine\" target=\"_blank\">with the potential to eclipse</a> Cabometyx as EXEL\u2019s top revenue generator.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">EXEL also received a <a href=\"https://ir.exelixis.com/news-releases/news-release-details/exelixis-announces-update-second-patent-litigation-trial-msn#:~:text=Additionally%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that,Morrissey%20%2C%20Ph.\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"https://ir.exelixis.com/news-releases/news-release-details/exelixis-announces-update-second-patent-litigation-trial-msn#:~:text=Additionally%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that,Morrissey%20%2C%20Ph.\" target=\"_blank\">favorable court ruling</a> last month when a U.S. District Court struck down a challenge from MSN Laboratories Private Limited against three patents with the Food and Drug Administration related to Cabometyx.</p> <h3 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">EXEL Valuation, Growth, and Profitability</h3> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The company is trading at an attractive valuation with a price-to-earnings-growth ratio (TTM) of 0.05, representing a 94.83% difference from the sector, and a price-to-earnings ratio (TTM) of 23.55 vs. the sector\u2019s 32.09. Additionally, EXEL has an EV/EBIT (TTM) ratio of 15.48, a 27.14% difference from the sector median of 21.24, suggesting that the stock trades at a discount relative to the market. Impressive year-over-year return on equity growth of 430.82%, a stark difference from the sector\u2019s -2.34%, indicates a healthy return on equity thus far.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Meanwhile, (FWD) diluted EPS compound annual growth of 43.47% over the next three years\u2014a 466.11% difference from the sector\u2014and an \u2018A+\u2019-rated EPS long-term growth rate of 32.96% over the next three to five years suggest that analysts agree that there is a strong growth pipeline ahead.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">EXEL is also highly profitable, with an <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EXEL/profitability\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EXEL/profitability\" target=\"_blank\">\u2018A+\u2019 grade</a> in the category thanks to an impressive $420.2M in cash from operations, a net income margin (TTM) of 22.43%, and an EBIT margin (TTM) of 29.22%\u2014a 1,081.73% difference from the 2.47% sector median.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The biotech group also has 30.06 cash per share (TTM) versus the sector\u2019s 1.32 and YoY levered cash flow of more than 360%, so it makes sense why 11 analysts have <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EXEL/earnings/revisions\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EXEL/earnings/revisions\" target=\"_blank\">revised up</a> in the last 90 days with EPS projected to grow more than 53% in FY24.</p> <figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_559bb6b1a49b98733650fe3a1b8259a2.jpeg\" rel=\"lightbox\" title=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_559bb6b1a49b98733650fe3a1b8259a2.jpeg\" target=\"_blank\" data-width=\"1600\" data-height=\"898\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_559bb6b1a49b98733650fe3a1b8259a2_thumb1.jpeg\" alt=\"chart\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Seeking Alpha Premium</span></p></figcaption></figure><h3 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">2. Tenet Healthcare Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THC\" title=\"Tenet Healthcare Corporation\">THC</a>)</h3> <ul class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> <li><p>Market Capitalization: $10.41B</p></li> <li><p>Quant Rating: Strong Buy</p></li> <li><p>Quant Sector Ranking (as of 12/3/24): 40 out of 1020</p></li> <li><p>Quant Industry Ranking (as of 12/3/24): 1 out of 497</p></li> </ul> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Included on my list of <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4717453-top-value-stocks-with-growth-prospects\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4717453-top-value-stocks-with-growth-prospects\" target=\"_blank\">Top Five Value Stocks With Growth Prospects</a> back in August, Tenet Healthcare is still on my radar, driven by A\u2019s in Valuation, Profitability, and Momentum</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Ranked #1 among SA Quant\u2019s <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/9409aeddb1-Top-Health-Care-Facilities-Stocks?source=first_level_url%3Asymbol%7Csection%3AQuant_Ranking%7Csection_asset%3AQuant_Ranking%7Cbutton%3Aindustry_rank\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/9409aeddb1-Top-Health-Care-Facilities-Stocks?source=first_level_url%3Asymbol%7Csection%3AQuant_Ranking%7Csection_asset%3AQuant_Ranking%7Cbutton%3Aindustry_rank\" target=\"_blank\">Top Health Care Facilities Stocks</a>, the Texas-based diversified healthcare services company\u2019s stock has surged nearly 115% over the last year and around 28% since making SA Quant\u2019s <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4693340-top-stocks-by-sector-sa-quant\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4693340-top-stocks-by-sector-sa-quant\" target=\"_blank\">Top Stocks by Sector</a> list in May.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The company has made strides in terms of lowering its debt, selling <a href=\"https://investor.tenethealth.com/press-releases/press-release-details/2024/Tenet-Completes-Sale-of-Six-Hospitals-in-California/default.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"https://investor.tenethealth.com/press-releases/press-release-details/2024/Tenet-Completes-Sale-of-Six-Hospitals-in-California/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">off six hospitals</a> in California as it refocuses on higher-margin areas. Those efforts were reflected in its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4218540-tenet-healthcare-stock-jumps-on-q3-earnings-raised-guidance\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4218540-tenet-healthcare-stock-jumps-on-q3-earnings-raised-guidance\" target=\"_blank\">better-than-expected Q3 earnings results</a>, which beat analyst earnings-per-share (EPS) estimates by 114% and revenue estimates by 1.4%. THC raised its fiscal 2024 adjusted EBITDA forecast to a range of $3.9B to $4B\u2014up from $50M previously\u2014and reported adjusted EPS is expected to be between $11.12 and $11.73, on operating revenue ranging from $20.6B to $20.8B, as a result of recent cost-cutting measures.</p> <h3 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">THC Valuation, Growth, and Profitability</h3> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">THC\u2019s \u2018Strong Buy\u2019 status can be attributed to its stellar <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THC/valuation/metrics\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THC/valuation/metrics\" target=\"_blank\">Valuation Scorecard</a>. Both GAAP and non-GAAP P/E ratios are discounted well below sector medians. With a PEG (TTM) of just 0.01, a -99.27% difference from the sector median of 1.03, THC shares are trading at a deep discount relative to its peers Its PEG (FWD) of 0.57, representing an -84.57% discount from the sector, and a price/cash flow of 7.37 vs. the sector\u2019s 16.06, also serve as compelling value metrics.</p> <figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_a736747ca9f37215c1cc2b00b32bc764.jpeg\" rel=\"lightbox\" title=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_a736747ca9f37215c1cc2b00b32bc764.jpeg\" target=\"_blank\" data-width=\"1600\" data-height=\"1146\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/3/saupload_a736747ca9f37215c1cc2b00b32bc764_thumb1.jpeg\" alt=\"chart\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Seeking Alpha Premium</span></p></figcaption></figure> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">THC is also highly profitable, boasting $3.2B in cash from operations and a 10.64% return on total assets (TTM)\u201426.95% less than the rest of the sector. The return on common equity (TTM), 118.01%, 40.83% higher than the rest of the sector, indicates a healthy flow of shareholder payouts.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The healthcare group\u2019s growth metrics are also compelling. THC\u2019s <span>(FWD)</span> diluted EPS compound annual growth rate is more than 614% vs. the sector median of 9.67%. In the last 90 days, 14 analysts have <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THC/earnings/revisions\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THC/earnings/revisions\" target=\"_blank\">revised up</a> their expectations of the company, with EPS projected to grow more than 60% in FY24.</p> <h2 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Conclusion</h2> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">While Wall Street has widely benefited from Washington\u2019s changing landscape thus far, healthcare stocks have been plunged into uncertainty as investors weigh the prospect of potential funding cuts and changes in leadership.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">But the fundamental demand for advanced healthcare technologies and modernization remains very strong, and the current sell-off has created ample opportunities for value plays if you know where to look.</p> <div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder paywall-full-content invisible\"></div> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">SA Quant can help you filter out the hidden gems using stock screens to suit your specific investment objectives. Consider using<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners?source=position_defensively%7Cscreeners\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners?source=position_defensively%7Cscreeners\" target=\"_blank\"> Seeking Alpha's 'Ratings Screener' tool</a> to help find stocks that achieve diversification into desired sectors you like. Or, if you\u2019re seeking a limited number of monthly ideas, consider exploring <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/alpha-picks/subscribe?hasComeFromMpArticle=true&amp;source=content_type%253Areact%257Csection%253Amain_content%257Cbutton%253Abody_link\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/alpha-picks/subscribe?hasComeFromMpArticle=true&amp;source=content_type%253Areact%257Csection%253Amain_content%257Cbutton%253Abody_link\" target=\"_blank\">Alpha Picks</a>.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2148728482/image_2148728482.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742173-buy-the-post-election-healthcare-dip-with-these-stocks", "pub_date": "2024-12-05 13:00:00"}]}